40|$|Abstract—New {{lead-free}} ferroelectric relaxor ceramics {{were prepared}} by conventional solid-state synthesis in the BaTiO 3 -Bi 2 O 3 -Y 2 O 3 systems. Some of these ceramics present a ferroelectric relaxor with transition temperature close to room temperature. These new materials are very interesting for applications and can replace leadbased ceramic {{to prevent the}} <b>toxic</b> <b>pollutions</b> during the preparation state. In the other hand, the energy band diagram shows the potentiality of these compounds for the solar energy conversion. Thus, some compositions have been tested successfully for H 2 production upon visible light. The best activity occurs in alkaline media with a rate evolution of about 0. 15 mL g- 1 mn- 1 and a quantum yield of 1 % under polychromatic light...|$|R
